cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.SY, cs.RO 

The paper deals with algorithms for batch reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of machine learning and artificial intelligence. The focus is on performance guarantees and theoretical analysis of the algorithms, which suggests that it belongs to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The use of stationary policies and error propagation also suggests a connection to control systems (cs.SY) and robotics (cs.RO).
